Architecture plan for issue #33

Scope
- Add two static numeral rings to the existing inline SVG analog clock face.
- Keep the app plain HTML, CSS, and JavaScript with no build step, backend, or
  database.
- Preserve the current clock hand IDs and JavaScript rotation behavior.

Module structure and file organization
- index.html
  - Remains the page shell and owns the inline SVG clock structure.
  - Add 24 static SVG text elements inside #clock: 12 Roman numerals on an
    outer ring and 12 Arabic numerals on an inner ring.
  - Place numerals with precomputed x/y values so rendering does not depend on
    client-side geometry code.
- styles.css
  - Add shared .numeral styling plus targeted .roman and .arabic variations.
  - Keep numeral text centered with SVG text-anchor and dominant-baseline.
  - Choose modest font sizes and colors that keep the rings readable without
    competing with ticks or hands.
- clock.js
  - No functional change expected.
  - Existing runtime selectors for #hand-hour, #hand-minute, and #hand-second
    must continue to work after the SVG markup changes.
- tests
  - Extend browser or DOM-oriented coverage to confirm both numeral rings are
    present, count 12 labels each, and do not break hand rendering.
  - Keep existing angle, render, and Playwright coverage intact.

Shared types and contracts
- There are no new shared types.
- The stable DOM contract remains the SVG #clock element plus hand elements
  #hand-hour, #hand-minute, and #hand-second.
- New styling hooks are class="numeral roman" and class="numeral arabic".

Dependencies between issues
- Only issue #33 is in scope for this batch, so there are no cross-issue
  dependencies.
- Implementation depends on the existing SVG face and tests already present in
  the repository.

Key design decisions
- Use static SVG text rather than JavaScript-generated numerals so the clock
  works when opened directly from disk and remains inspectable.
- Keep numeral coordinates precomputed in index.html to match the issue
  request and avoid adding geometry helpers to clock.js.
- Insert numeral elements before the hand elements so hands render above both
  rings.
- Avoid extra dependencies or layout abstractions; this is a narrow SVG markup
  and CSS enhancement.
